{"updated_at": {"date": {"d": "28", "m": "06", "Y": "2026"}, "time": {"H": "16", "M": "56", "S": "00"}}, "news": [{"title": "Embassy Developments to invest \u20b91,500 crore to build three million sq ft office space in Bengaluru", "para": "Embassy Developments is investing Rs 1,500 crore to build a 3 million sq ft office complex in Bengaluru, aiming to boost rental income from commercial assets. This move complements their strong residential business, which saw sales bookings more than double last fiscal. The company plans to launch nearly Rs 20,000 crore worth of homes this fiscal, targeting robust consumer demand.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/commercial/embassy-developments-to-invest-1500-crore-in-3-million-sq-ft-office-space-in-bengaluru/132055340?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-903215/132055340.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "commercial"}, {"title": "UP RERA issues notices to promoters of 76 projects over non-filing of annual audit reports", "para": "Promoters are required to upload annual audit reports of project accounts on the UP RERA portal within six months from the end of a financial year. Non-filing attracts a late fee of \u20b925,000, while violation of relevant RERA provisions can attract penalty of up to 5% of the estimated project cost.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/rera/up-rera-cracks-down-on-76-real-estate-promoters-for-missing-annual-audit-reports/132055527?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-229336/132055527.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "rera"}, {"title": "Homebuyers can seek relief for delay after possession: Supreme Court", "para": "Homebuyers can still seek compensation for delayed flat possession even after taking custody, the Supreme Court ruled. The apex court set aside a previous order stating homebuyers cease to be consumers post-possession. It also clarified that arbitration clauses in agreements do not prevent buyers from approaching consumer forums for grievances. This landmark decision revives a 22-year-old case, emphasizing that contractual clauses cannot override statutory remedies.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/regulatory/supreme-court-ruling-homebuyers-can-claim-compensation-after-property-possession-delay/132028561?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-833578/132028561.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "regulatory"}]}